    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-27T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-27T02:35:00-05:00" n="467"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90H/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-27T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 27, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Personal for Murray. Arrival of new Afghan Ambassador here would afford
                    suitable opportunity to mention to him third paragraph of your 43, September 4,
                    3 p.m., provided your plans are taking shape.</p>
                <p>I have not yet referred to your proposed visit to Teheran as it would undoubtedly
                    be interpreted as in the nature of a special mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
